---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
const crewBody = `
  

  <!-- ============ SECTION 0: HERO ============ -->
  <header class="hero hero--with-image">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-grid">
        <div class="hero-text">
          <div class="hero-eyebrow eyebrow">Yacht Crew Mortgages</div>
          <h1 class="display-1">Yacht crew mortgage from a lender who counts charter tips, rotation savings, and ENG1 fitness.</h1>
          <p class="lead hero-subtitle">Yacht crew carry a mortgage file that almost no generalist lender knows how to read: a modest base salary that doubles or triples with charter tips, room-and-board fully covered by the vessel, a foreign-flagged W-2 from a Cayman or Marshall Islands management company, an STCW Basic Safety Training certificate plus ENG1 medical, savings accumulated across 3&ndash;5 charter seasons with almost no living expenses, and a five-to-seven-year career window before transitioning to land. Generalist lenders see the low base wage on the W-2, miss the tip income on Form 4137, and decline the file as "insufficient income." We read the SEA, the charter tip ledger, the ENG1 medical, and the rotation pattern &mdash; and we qualify you on what you actually take home including tips.</p>
