  <!-- ============ LEDE ============ -->
  <section class="lede-section">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <p class="lede">Stairway Mortgage qualifies yacht crew on the income they actually take home including tips &mdash; <strong>not just the base W-2 line that makes a $40K deckhand look like they can&rsquo;t afford a home</strong>. A junior deckhand with three charter seasons under their belt, a chief stew running interior on a 50m with declared tip income that exceeds base, a yacht chef on a 60m motor with HACCP credentials and charter command kitchen, and a former bosun transitioning to a marine-trades land career each get qualified using the method that fits their pay. We pick the right door before we quote. Or skip ahead: browse <a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-programs/" style="color: var(--blue); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px;">every loan program</a>, run numbers on <a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/loan-calculator/" style="color: var(--blue); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px;">100+ mortgage calculators</a>, or check <a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/current-rates/" style="color: var(--blue); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px;">today&apos;s rates</a>. For the parent hub and other yacht professions, see our <a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/yacht-professionals/" style="color: var(--blue); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px;">yacht professionals mortgage hub</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ H2 #1: KEY FACTS ============ -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header" style="text-align: center; max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto;">
        <div class="eyebrow">01 &middot; Yacht crew mortgage at a glance</div>
        <h2>Key facts every yacht crew member should know before applying for a mortgage.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="key-facts-grid">
        <div class="key-fact-card">
          <div class="key-fact-num">$46,720</div>
          <p class="key-fact-body">BLS median annual wage for deckhands &amp; marine oilers, the closest standard occupational category to entry yacht crew. Yacht crew typically earn 25&ndash;100% more once charter tips are included. Source: <a href="https://www.bls.gov/ooh/transportation-and-material-moving/water-transportation-occupations.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">BLS Water Transportation Occupations</a>.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="key-fact-card">
          <div class="key-fact-num">STCW + ENG1</div>
          <p class="key-fact-body">Two universal entry credentials required of all yacht crew. STCW Basic Safety Training (5-day mandatory course covering fire fighting, survival, first aid, personal safety) and the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/maritime-and-coastguard-agency" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ENG1 medical</a> certificate confirming fitness for sea duty.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="key-fact-card">
          <div class="key-fact-num">$1,500&ndash;$10K</div>
          <p class="key-fact-body">Per-charter tip pool range per week. Industry standard is 10&ndash;15% of charter fee distributed among crew. Captain takes 1.5&ndash;2 shares; chief stew &amp; chef take 1.25&ndash;1.5 shares; deckhand &amp; stew take 1 share. <a href="https://www.irs.gov/businesses/small-businesses-self-employed/tip-recordkeeping-and-reporting" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">IRS tip reporting</a> rules require declaration.</p>
        </div>
