          <div class="key-fact-num">FBAR + 8938</div>
          <p class="key-fact-body">U.S. citizen crew paid into foreign accounts must file FinCEN 114 (FBAR) and IRS <a href="https://www.irs.gov/businesses/comparison-of-form-8938-and-fbar-requirements" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Form 8938</a>. The filings don&rsquo;t affect mortgage qualification but signal a multi-jurisdiction tax picture generalist lenders mishandle.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ H2 #2: ROLE-TIER SOLUTIONS ============ -->
  <section class="professions-section section-tinted">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header" style="text-align: center; max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto;">
        <div class="eyebrow">02 &middot; Where you are in the crew hierarchy</div>
        <h2>Yacht crew mortgage solutions for every role tier.</h2>
        <p>Crew isn&rsquo;t one job &mdash; it&rsquo;s a family of roles across deck, interior, galley, and specialty departments. Each tier has its own qualifying logic.</p>
